==English==

===Etymology===
From Ancient Greek [[α-|αν-]] ''(an)'' ([[without]]), [[αρχός]] ''(archos)'' ([[leader]], [[governance]], [[rulership]]).

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# Any theory or doctrine that proposes the [[absence]] of involuntary [[government]] in all forms.
# ''Specifically'', a political philosophical belief that all forms of involuntary rule or government are [[undesirable]] or [[unnecessary]] and that society could function without a ruler or government in a [[socialism|socialist]] order, perhaps with a non-hierarchical leadership (possibly only present for reasons of keeping peace and defense).

